    "description": "Configure Custom AI presets for metadata generation.",
    "content": "Custom AI presets save **AI instructions**, **description templates**, and **blocks** (CTA, Links, Disclaimer) per platform so you can reuse them when generating metadata. Presets are managed in **Settings** → **Custom AI**. The **active** preset (or the custom settings you last applied) is used when you run **Generate** — both for the AI pipeline and for formatting the exported description files. Click **Settings** in the **top toolbar**, then choose **Custom AI**. The dialog shows the preset dropdown, preset name field, and three tabs: **AI Instructions**, **Description Template**, and **Blocks**. - **Preset** dropdown: select an existing preset or **None**. The active preset is marked **(active)**. - **Preset name** field: used when creating a new preset. - **Save as new**: save the current draft as a new preset (name required). The new preset becomes active. - **Update preset**: overwrite the currently selected preset with the current draft. - **Delete**: remove the selected preset. If it was active, active is cleared. - **AI Instructions** tab: choose **Platform** (All / YouTube / Instagram / TikTok) and enter custom instructions for the AI (max 1000 characters per field). Used when the pipeline generates title, description, and hashtags. - **Description Template** tab: choose **Platform** and enter a template with placeholders. The generated description is built from this template after generation. - **Blocks** tab: choose **Platform** and set **CTA**, **Links**, and **Disclaimer** text. These are injected into the description template at &#123;CTA&#125; , &#123;LINKS&#125; , &#123;DISCLAIMER&#125; . Click **Apply** to save the current draft to the app’s Custom AI settings. If the draft matches the selected preset, that preset is set as **active**; otherwise the active preset is cleared (custom settings still apply). The **active** preset (or last applied custom settings) is used when you run **Generate** from the **Details** panel or via **Publish** → **Metadata only** → **Generate**: the pipeline uses your instructions, then the description files are formatted with your template and blocks (CTA, Links, Disclaimer). **Placeholders in description template** Use &#123;TITLE&#125; , &#123;DESCRIPTION&#125; , &#123;HASHTAGS&#125; , &#123;CTA&#125; , &#123;LINKS&#125; , &#123;DISCLAIMER&#125; . They are replaced with the generated title/description/hashtags and with the CTA/Links/Disclaimer blocks from your preset. Unknown placeholders are removed. **Per-platform values** Instructions, description template, and blocks support **All** plus overrides for **YouTube**, **Instagram**, and **TikTok**. The app merges “All” with the platform-specific value when generating or formatting for each platform. **Common issues** - **Preset not applied when generating** — Select the preset in the dropdown, then click **Apply** so it becomes active (or use **Save as new** to create and activate it). - **Save as new** requires a preset name; **Update preset** requires a preset to be selected. - **Reset to default** clears instructions, template, and blocks in the dialog; it does not delete presets."
